  "texts": [
    "On the DBLP, deep graph convolutional neural network D2GCN (semantic) based on text feature is better than deep graph convolutional neural network D2GCN (structure) based on structural features.",
    "Because the number of neighboring nodes of the central node is smaller, but the probability that they belong to the same type is higher.",
    "Therefore, the baseline methods are better than the proposed D2GCN when the number of convolution layer is 2.",
    "However, D2GCN also increases model performance as the increasing number of graph convolutional layers.",
    "Other baseline methods show a tendency that the accuracy first rises and then decreases in the classification task, or show an unstable phenomenon of alternating ascent and descent."
  ],
